    <h1 id = "title">Elephant</h1>
    <p>Elephants are mammals of the family Elephantidae and the largest existing land animals. </p>
    <figure id="img-div">
      <img id="image" src = "https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcQFs0ruHzZozZe6itdcF8kqXvAw4aIU56RgKA&usqp=CAU>"
<figcaption id="img-caption">
      Elephants are the largest land animals on Earth, and they're one of the most unique-looking animals, too. With their characteristic long noses, or trunks; large, floppy ears; and wide, thick legs, there is no other animal with a similar physique.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  <section id="tribute-info">
    <h3 id="headline">Here is the detailed about Elephant.</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Length</strong>- Asian elephant: 5.5 – 6.5 m</li>
      <li><strong>Phylum</strong> -Chordata</li>
      <li><strong>Gestation period</strong> - African bush elephant: 22 months, Asian elephant: 18 – 22 months</li>
      <li><strong>Lifespan</strong> African bush elephant: 60 – 70 years, Asian elephant: 48 years, African forest elephant: 60 – 70 years</li>
      <li><strong>Mass</strong>African bush elephant: 6,000 kg, Asian elephant: 4,000 kg, African forest elephant: 2,700 kg</li>
      <li><strong>Height</strong>African bush elephant: 3.2 m, Asian elephant: 2.7 m</li>
    </ul>
    <blockquote cite = "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elephant">
      <p>
        Elephants are the largest land animals on Earth, and they're one of the most unique-looking animals, too. With their characteristic long noses, or trunks; large, floppy ears; and wide, thick legs, there is no other animal with a similar physique.
      </p>
      <cite>-- Elephant History</cite>  
      <h3>If you have time, you should read more about this incredible animal in 
